        "text": "For the purposes of this analysis, we replace those dichotomies of early, anti- or otherwise bourgeois social theory with the more abstract dichotomy of system and environment inherent in the concept of system. It is through this difference that complexity is constituted, serving at the same time as the ultimate point of reference and integration for functional analyses. In the case of social systems, we are dealing with a special form of processing system/environment differences, namely sense. On sense rests the possibility of conceiving complexity as indeterminate determinability - the very problem that precedes the tradition obscured by metaphysics and that is to be introduced explicitly into social theory."
